summary: September 23 is the 266th day of the year  in the Gregorian calendar.
full_text:
September 23 is the 266th day of the year  in the Gregorian calendar. There are 99 days remaining until the end of the year.
It is frequently the day of the autumnal equinox in the Northern Hemisphere and the day of the vernal equinox in the Southern Hemisphere.
title: September 23
